    <blocks>028</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, refactoring, chat</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Deletes production chat-tool classes; refactors callers to route through generic `invoke_playbook`; high blast-radius (similar to Q9 batch but scoped); tags `bff-api`+`ai`+`refactoring`.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent file deletions/refactors; gates 028 integration test.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Remove `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` and `InvokeInsightsQueryTool` specialized C# bridge
    classes. Route all existing callers through the generic `invoke_playbook` chat tool
    (tasks 021 + 022). For the Insights case, `InsightsIntentClassifier` continues to handle
    playbook-vs-RAG routing internally — the generic tool dispatches to whichever execution
    path the playbook's metadata indicates per FR-24.

    Critical-path context: this task closes Pillar 3. After it lands, the chat-side has one
    canonical tool for invoking playbooks (`invoke_playbook`) — eliminating the specialized
    bridge proliferation that R5 closed with as a known limitation.

    Risk: any caller still referencing the removed classes will break. Use Grep extensively
    to find all references; update each to call `invoke_playbook` via the data-driven tool
    path. Regression tests for /summarize chat path + insights query chat path MUST pass
    after the refactor — these are the user-visible flows that depend on the bridge being
    cleanly replaced.

    Rollback plan (light): `git revert` of this PR restores the bridge classes; document
    in task notes.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with chat-architecture + InsightsIntentClassifier familiarity.
    Comfortable with cross-cutting refactor + Grep-driven dependency tracking.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool.cs` + `InvokeInsightsQueryTool.cs` deleted. All callers
    updated to use generic `invoke_playbook` tool path. Regression tests for /summarize
    chat path + insights query chat path pass. Build green; publish-size delta reported
    (net negative expected).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
